Install Visual Studio Code
Install Node.js
Install Vue CLI (Command Line Interface)
# npm install -g @vue/cli
Create a Vue Project
# vue create [my-vue-project_name]
Note: Choose the default preset or manually configure project.
Navigate to the Project Directory
# cd [my-vue-project_name]
Open the Project in Visual Studio Code
Use the terminal to open the project directory
# code .
Install VSCode Extensions (Optional)
Some popular extensions for Vue.js development include "Vetur," "Vue 3 Snippets," and "Vue VSCode Snippets."
Start the Development Server
# npm run serve
Start Coding



